# Onboarding tour steps
onboarding-step-entry-toolbar-stage = AI Butler Dashboard
onboarding-step-entry-toolbar-title = AI Butler Dashboard
onboarding-step-entry-toolbar-description = The 🤖 button on the library toolbar opens the AI Butler dashboard. Click the real button directly, and the tutorial will move to the next step automatically.
onboarding-step-entry-toolbar-fallback = If you do not see the 🤖 button, make sure you are in the main Zotero library window and wait for the plugin toolbar to finish loading.
onboarding-step-content-dashboard-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-content-dashboard-title = Dashboard content area
onboarding-step-content-dashboard-description = After clicking 🤖, the dashboard opens by default. The top area shows Butler status and processing statistics, and the lower area contains quick actions. You will use one-click setup here later.
onboarding-step-page-summary-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-page-summary-title = Page 2: AI Summary
onboarding-step-page-summary-description = Click the highlighted “AI Summary” tab. The next step will show the AI Summary content area.
onboarding-step-content-summary-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-content-summary-title = AI Summary content area
onboarding-step-content-summary-description = This area shows summary output, follow-up questions, and summary results. When you open it from a paper context menu or the sidebar, you will see the full generation process here.
onboarding-step-page-tasks-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-page-tasks-title = Page 3: Task Queue
onboarding-step-page-tasks-description = Click the highlighted “Task Queue” tab. The next step will show the task queue content area.
onboarding-step-content-tasks-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-content-tasks-title = Task Queue content area
onboarding-step-content-tasks-description = This area lists running, pending, completed, and failed tasks. When you import PDFs, generate summaries, or run Deep Reading, you can return here to check progress.
onboarding-step-page-settings-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-page-settings-title = Page 4: Quick Settings
onboarding-step-page-settings-description = Click the highlighted “Quick Settings” tab. The next step will show the Quick Settings content area.
onboarding-step-content-settings-stage = Four Pages
onboarding-step-content-settings-title = Quick Settings content area
onboarding-step-content-settings-description = This is the Quick Settings page. The left side lists setting categories, and the right side shows all options for the selected category. Next, you will open “Model Platform” to test DeepSeek.
onboarding-step-setup-go-dashboard-stage = Initial Setup
onboarding-step-setup-go-dashboard-title = Prepare the model configuration
onboarding-step-setup-go-dashboard-description = Next, use “One-click setup” on the dashboard to write the DeepSeek endpoint, model, and API key. Click the real “Dashboard” tab at the top to return to quick actions.
onboarding-step-setup-open-stage = Initial Setup
onboarding-step-setup-open-title = Use one-click setup for DeepSeek first
onboarding-step-setup-open-description = Click the highlighted “One-click setup” button and paste your DeepSeek API key in the wizard. After completion, the wizard creates a DeepSeek endpoint and continues to the next stage.
onboarding-step-setup-open-fallback = If you do not see the button, click the “Dashboard” tab at the top first, then click “One-click setup”.
onboarding-step-model-go-settings-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-go-settings-title = Prepare to verify the model
onboarding-step-model-go-settings-description = After DeepSeek setup is complete, confirm that the model endpoint can return a result. Click the real “Quick Settings” tab at the top to open model-related settings.
onboarding-step-model-platform-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-platform-title = View the DeepSeek endpoint in Model Platform
onboarding-step-model-platform-description = Model Platform manages all providers and endpoints. Click “Model Platform” on the left and find the DeepSeek configuration created by one-click setup.
onboarding-step-model-deepseek-card-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-deepseek-card-title = Check the DeepSeek details
onboarding-step-model-deepseek-card-description = To verify the endpoint, model, and PDF processing mode written by one-click setup, click the real “Details” button on the DeepSeek card to expand the configuration.
onboarding-step-model-deepseek-card-fallback = If you do not see the DeepSeek card, complete one-click setup in the previous stage first.
onboarding-step-model-detail-overview-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-detail-overview-title = This is the DeepSeek configuration you just created
onboarding-step-model-detail-overview-description = The details include API URL, API key, model name, PDF processing mode, and related options. First confirm that these values came from the one-click setup.
onboarding-step-model-scroll-to-test-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-scroll-to-test-title = Scroll down to the connection test
onboarding-step-model-scroll-to-test-description = Use the mouse wheel in the Model Platform detail area to scroll down through the DeepSeek configuration until you see the “Connection Test / Test Connection” button. The tutorial will continue when it appears.
onboarding-step-model-test-button-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-test-button-title = Test the DeepSeek connection
onboarding-step-model-test-button-description = Click “Test Connection” to confirm that the API key, model, and network are available. The next step will show the connection test result so you can confirm the model returned content.
onboarding-step-model-test-result-stage = Test the Model
onboarding-step-model-test-result-title = Review the DeepSeek response
onboarding-step-model-test-result-description = This is the connection test result area. Green success text means DeepSeek returned a response and can be used for AI Summary and Deep Reading. Red errors usually mean the API key, model name, API URL, or network needs attention. If it still says “Testing...”, wait a few seconds.
onboarding-step-model-test-result-fallback = If you do not see a test result yet, click “Test Connection” above and wait for the model response.
onboarding-step-model-to-library-transition-stage = Import Papers
onboarding-step-model-to-library-transition-title = Move on to importing papers
onboarding-step-model-to-library-transition-description = The model is ready. Next, return to the Zotero library and import a PDF so AI Butler can create a summary task automatically.
onboarding-step-collection-area-stage = Import Papers
onboarding-step-collection-area-title = The left pane is the collections area: create a collection first
onboarding-step-collection-area-description = The collections pane is on the left. Create a collection first so the imported PDF and generated AI notes have a clear place to live.
onboarding-step-collection-area-next = Next
onboarding-step-collection-area-fallback = Follow this step to continue the AI Butler onboarding tutorial.
onboarding-step-paper-area-drop-stage = Import Papers
onboarding-step-paper-area-drop-title = The middle pane is the items area: drag a PDF here
onboarding-step-paper-area-drop-description = Drag a PDF into the middle items area. Zotero may fetch metadata first, and AI Butler will create a summary task after the PDF attachment is ready.
onboarding-step-paper-area-drop-fallback = Drag a PDF into the middle items area. If Zotero is still fetching metadata such as title, authors, or DOI, the tutorial will wait here.
onboarding-step-task-open-dashboard-stage = Import Papers
onboarding-step-task-open-dashboard-title = View the summary task progress
onboarding-step-task-open-dashboard-description = After the PDF is imported, open AI Butler from the 🤖 toolbar entry to view summary task progress.
onboarding-step-task-open-dashboard-fallback = If you do not see the 🤖 button, make sure you are in the main Zotero library window and wait for the plugin toolbar to finish loading.
onboarding-step-task-progress-stage = Import Papers
onboarding-step-task-progress-title = Find the summary task for the imported paper
onboarding-step-task-progress-description = Open the Task Queue and find the summary task created for the PDF you just imported.
onboarding-step-summary-task-progress-stage = Import Papers
onboarding-step-summary-task-progress-title = Check the current summary progress
onboarding-step-summary-task-progress-description = The task card shows extraction, model generation, note saving, and completion progress. Move the mouse over the stage label to see more details.
onboarding-step-summary-task-progress-fallback = If the task is still pending, wait a moment or check the model configuration from Quick Settings.
onboarding-step-summary-close-dashboard-stage = View the Summary
onboarding-step-summary-close-dashboard-title = Return to the items area to view the summary
onboarding-step-summary-close-dashboard-description = Close the AI Butler dashboard and return to the Zotero items area. Next, you will select the imported paper and inspect the generated summary.
onboarding-step-select-paper-stage = View the Summary
onboarding-step-select-paper-title = Select the paper you just imported
onboarding-step-select-paper-description = Select the paper you just imported in the items list. The item pane on the right will show Zotero metadata and the AI Butler sidebar entry.
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-stage = View the Summary
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-title = Open the AI Butler sidebar for this paper
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-description = Open the AI Butler section in the item pane. It gathers paper actions, AI notes, table summaries, image summaries, mind maps, and quick chat.
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-fallback = If the sidebar section is collapsed, expand the AI Butler section in Zotero’s item pane for the selected paper.
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-content-stage = View the Summary
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-content-title = This is the AI Butler sidebar
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-content-description = The sidebar lets you quickly view generated notes, start follow-up actions, and jump back to the main AI Butler window.
onboarding-step-sidebar-ai-butler-content-fallback = Follow this step to continue the AI Butler onboarding tutorial.
onboarding-step-collection-export-stage = Export AI notes from the collection to local files
onboarding-step-collection-export-title = Export AI notes from the collection to local files
onboarding-step-collection-export-description = The collection context menu can export generated AI Summary and Deep Reading notes in bulk. Right-click the collection you created and choose the AI note export action. You can adjust the default directory and format later in Quick Settings.
onboarding-step-paper-deep-read-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-paper-deep-read-title = Start AI Deep Reading for an important paper
onboarding-step-paper-deep-read-description = Deep Reading is useful for important papers that need deeper understanding. Right-click this paper in the item list and choose the Deep Reading or re-run Deep Reading action from AI Butler.
onboarding-step-paper-deep-read-fallback = Select a paper and right-click it first. If the context menu is not open yet, this step highlights the item list area.
onboarding-step-deep-read-open-dashboard-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-deep-read-open-dashboard-title = View Deep Reading task progress
onboarding-step-deep-read-open-dashboard-description = The Deep Reading task has started. Next, confirm in the task queue whether the multi-round reading task is pending, running, or completed. Click the 🤖 AI Butler entry on the library toolbar to open the dashboard.
onboarding-step-deep-read-open-dashboard-fallback = If you do not see the 🤖 button, make sure you are in the main Zotero library window and wait for the plugin toolbar to finish loading.
onboarding-step-deep-read-tasks-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-deep-read-tasks-title = Confirm the Deep Reading task status
onboarding-step-deep-read-tasks-description = The task queue shows whether the Deep Reading task is pending, running, completed, or failed. Click the “Task Queue” tab at the top to confirm the task you just started.
onboarding-step-deep-read-explain-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-deep-read-explain-title = AI Deep Reading: read the paper in depth
onboarding-step-deep-read-explain-description = AI Deep Reading splits the paper into multiple reading rounds and calls the model API several times to read the paper in depth. Progress stages include waiting, extracting PDF, planning rounds, AI Deep Reading 3/25, and saving notes. Hover over a stage such as “AI Deep Reading 3/25” to see detailed progress.
onboarding-step-deep-read-explain-fallback = AI Deep Reading calls the model in multiple rounds for deeper paper analysis. If the task list is not visible yet, keep the Task Queue page open and wait.
onboarding-step-final-settings-tab-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-final-settings-tab-title = Continue exploring Quick Settings
onboarding-step-final-settings-tab-description = The core workflow is complete. Quick Settings also contains model platform, auto scan, note export, sidebar display, context menu, and other personalization options. Click the “Quick Settings” tab at the top.
onboarding-step-final-settings-catalog-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-final-settings-catalog-title = The left side lists configurable sections
onboarding-step-final-settings-catalog-description = This catalog contains Model Platform, API Configuration, Prompts, One-Image Summary, automatic note export, UI Settings, Data Management, and more. When you want to adjust AI Butler behavior later, this is usually the place to start.
onboarding-step-final-ui-settings-nav-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-final-ui-settings-nav-title = Open UI Settings
onboarding-step-final-ui-settings-nav-description = UI Settings lets you adjust auto scan, context menu actions, sidebar display, and how existing notes are handled. Click “UI Settings” on the left.
onboarding-step-final-auto-deepread-setting-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-final-auto-deepread-setting-title = Generate AI Deep Reading during auto scan
onboarding-step-final-auto-deepread-setting-description = This option automatically adds newly imported papers to the AI Deep Reading queue. It is useful for focused reading workflows, but Deep Reading calls the model multiple times and consumes noticeably more tokens than a normal summary. Enable it only if it fits your workflow.
onboarding-step-final-auto-deepread-setting-next = Got it
onboarding-step-final-auto-deepread-setting-fallback = You can find “Generate AI Deep Reading during auto scan” in UI Settings. It consumes more tokens, so you do not need to enable it now; just note what it does.
onboarding-step-finish-stage = Deep Reading
onboarding-step-finish-title = 🎉 Congratulations, the tutorial is complete!
onboarding-step-finish-description = You have completed the core AI Butler workflow: configure a model, import a paper, view the summary, export notes, start Deep Reading, and check task status. You can replay the tutorial from the dashboard at any time.
onboarding-prev-button = Back
